maml:description.maml:para: Connect to Anypoint Platform with an authenticated account for use with cmdlets from the Anypoint PowerShell modules.

The Connect-ApAccount cmdlet connects to Anypoint Platform with an authenticated account for use with cmdlets from the Anypoint PowerShell modules. After executing this cmdlet, you can disconnect from an Anypoint Platform account using Disconnect-ApAccount.

command:example.maml:title: ------- Example 1: Connect to Anypoint with interactive -------
command:example.dev:code: PS C:\> Connect-ApAccount Username: maxthemule2020 Password: ********

command:example.maml:title: ------- Example 2: Connect to Anypoint using credential -------
command:example.dev:code:
PS C:\> $cred = Get-Credential
PowerShell credential request Enter your credentials. User: mulethemax2020 Password for user mulethemax2020: ********
PS C:\> Connect-ApAccount -Credential $cred

command:example.maml:title: ------ Example 3: Connect to Anypoint using access token ------
command:example.dev:code: PS C:\> Connect-ApAccount -AccessToken 'xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx'

command:example.maml:title: ----------- Example 4: Using 'Login-ApAccount' alias -----------
command:example.dev:code: PS C:\> Login-ApAccount Username: maxthemule2020 Password: ********

maml:description.maml:para: Disconnects a connected Anypoint Platform account.
The Disconnect-ApAccount cmdlet disconnects a connected Anypoint account. After executing this cmdlet, you will need to login again using Connect-ApAccount.

command:example.maml:title: ------------- Example 1: Disconnect from Anypoint -------------
command:example.dev:code: PS C:\> Disconnect-ApAccount

command:example.maml:title: ---------- Example 2: Using 'Logout-ApAccount' alias ----------
command:example.dev:code: PS C:\> Logout-ApAccount
